<L N="1296">With all &thorn;e woo &thorn;at prison may me &yogh;iue</L>
<L>And eek with peyne &thorn;at loue me yiue&thorn; also</L>
<L>That double&thorn; al my torment and my wo</L>
<L>Ther with &thorn;e fyr of gelousie vpsterte</L>
<L N="1300">With Inne his brest and hente him by &thorn;e herte</L>
<L>So woodly &thorn;at he lik was to byholde</L>
<L>The boxtre or &thorn;e asshen deed and colde</L>
<L>Than seide he o cruel goddes &thorn;at gouerne</L>
<L N="1304">This world with bynding of your word eterne</L>
<L>And writen in &thorn;e table of athamaunt</L>
<L>youre parlement and &yogh;our eterne graunt</L>
<L>What is mankynde more vnto &yogh;ou holde</L>
<L N="1308">Than is &thorn;e scheep &thorn;at rouke&thorn; in &thorn;e folde</L>
<L>ffor slain is man right as ano&thorn;er beeste</L>
<L>And dwelle&thorn; eek in prison and in arreste</L>
<L>And ha&thorn; siknesse and gret aduersite</L>
<L N="1312">And ofte tymes gilteles parde</L>
<L>&para; What gouernance is in &thorn;is prescience</L>
<L>That gilteles tormente&thorn; Innocence</L>
<L>And encreseth &thorn;is is al my penaunce</L>
<L N="1316">That man is bounden to his obseruaunce</L>
<L>ffor goddes sake to letten of his wille</L>
<L>Ther as a beeste may all his lust fulfille</L>
<L>And whan a beeste is ded he ha&thorn; no peyne</L>
<L N="1320">But after his deth &thorn;e man mot weepe and pleyne</L>
<L>Though in &thorn;is world he haue care and wo
<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="39"></L>
<L>Wi&thorn;outen doute it may stonden so</L>
<L>The answere of &thorn;is lete I to diuines</L>
<L N="1324">But wel I wot &thorn;at in &thorn;is world gret pyne is</L>
<L>Allas I see a serpent or a &thorn;eef</L>
<L>That many a trewe man ha&thorn; do meschief</L>
<L>Gon at his large and wher him list may turne</L>
<L N="1328">But I moot ben in prison &thorn;urgh Saturne</L>
<L>And eek &thorn;urgh Iuno Ialous and eek wood</L>
<L>That ha&thorn; destroyed wel neyh al &thorn;e blood<MILESTONE N="19b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Of Thebes with his waste walles wide</L>
<L N="1332">And venus slee&thorn; me on &thorn;at o&thorn;er syde</L>
<L>ffor Ialousye and fere of him Arcite</L>
<L>&para; Now wil I stynte of Palamon alite</L>
<L>And lat him in his prison stille dwelle</L>
<L N="1336">And of Arcite for&thorn; I wil &yogh;ou telle</L>
<L>The somer passe&thorn; and &thorn;e nightes longe</L>
<L>Encresceth double wise &thorn;e peynes stronge</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e of &thorn;e louer and of &thorn;e prisoner</L>
<L N="1340">I not which ha&thorn; &thorn;e wofuller myster</L>
<L>ffor schortly for to sein of Palamon</L>
<L>Perpetuelly is dampned to prison</L>
<L>In cheynes and in fettres to &thorn;e ded</L>
<L N="1344">And arcite is exiled vp his hed</L>
<L>ffor euermore as out of &thorn;at contre</L>
<L>Ne neuer he ne schal his lady se</L>
<L>&para; yow louers aske I now &thorn;is question</L>
<L N="1348">Who ha&thorn; &thorn;e wors arcite or Palam&omacr;n</L>
<L>That oon may seen his lady day by day</L>
<L>But in prison moot he duellen ay</L>
<L>That o&thorn;er wher him list may ride or go</L>
<L N="1352">But seen his lady schal he neuer mo</L>
<L>Now diuineth as &yogh;ou list &thorn;at &yogh;e can</L>
<L>ffor I wol telle forth as I bigan<NOTE PLACE="end">[No gap in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
