<L N="1436">Ther &thorn;at he might his vertu excercise</L>
<L>And &thorn;us withinne a while his name is spronge</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e of his deedes and of his goode tonge<MILESTONE N="21a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>That Theseus ha&thorn; taken him so neere</L>
<L N="1440">That of his Chambre he made him a squiere</L>
<L>And gaf him golde to mayntene his degre</L>
<L>And eek men brought him out of his contre</L>
<L>ffro &yogh;eer to &yogh;eer ful priuily his rente</L>
<L N="1444">But honestly and sleighly he it spente</L>
<L>That no man wondred how &thorn;at he it hadde</L>
<L>And &thorn;re &yogh;eer in &thorn;is wise his lif he ladde</L>
<L>And bar him so in pees and eek in werre</L>
<L N="1448">Ther was no man &thorn;at Theseus ha&thorn; derre</L>
