<L>The hertes of hir folk right as hire day</L>
<L>Is geerful right so chaunge&thorn; sche array</L>
<L>Seelde is &thorn;e fryday al &thorn;e wike y-like</L>
<L N="1540">&para; Whan &thorn;at arcite hadde songe he gan to syke</L>
<L>And sette him doun wi&thorn;outen eny more</L>
<L>Allas quod he &thorn;at day &thorn;at I was bore</L>
<L>How longe Iuno &thorn;urgh &thorn;i cruelte</L>
<L N="1544">Wiltow werreien Thebes &thorn;e Cite</L>
<L>Allas y-brought is to confusion</L>
<L>The blood Roial of Cadme and Amphion<MILESTONE N="22b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Of Cadmus which &thorn;at was &thorn;e ferste man</L>
<L N="1548">That Thebes bult or ferst &thorn;e toun bigan</L>
