<L N="1596">This arcite with ful despitous herte</L>
<L>When he him knew and hadde his tale herde</L>
<L>As fers as a leon pulled out a swerde</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;us by god &thorn;a[t] sitte&thorn; aboue</L>
<L N="1600">Nere it were &thorn;at &thorn;ou art sike and wood for loue</L>
<L>And eek &thorn;at &thorn;ou no wepne hast in &thorn;is place /</L>
<L>Thou schuldest neuer out of &thorn;is groue pace</L>
<L>That &thorn;ou ne schuldest deyen of myn honde</L>
<L N="1604">ffor I diffie &thorn;e sewrte and &thorn;e bonde
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="47"></L>
<L>Which &thorn;at &thorn;ou seist I haue maad to &thorn;e /</L>
