<L N="284">Wel may &thorn;is be a prouerbe of a schrewe</L>
<L>Thou seist &thorn;at Oxen assen hors and houndes</L>
<L>They ben assayed at diuerse stoundes</L>
<L>Bacynes lauours or &thorn;at men hem bye</L>
<L N="288">Spoones stooles and swich housbondrye</L>
<L>And so ben clo&thorn;es pottes and o&thorn;er arrayes</L>
<L>But of wommen aren maked non assayes<MILESTONE N="108a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>for</I> 103</NOTE></L>
<L>Til &thorn;ei ben wedded olde dotard schrewe</L>
