<L>What wenestow make an ydyot of oure dame /</L>
<L N="312">Now by &thorn;at lord &thorn;at called is seint Iame
<PB REF="00000250.tif" N="222"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="343"></L>
<L>&thorn;ou schalt not bo&thorn;e &thorn;ough &thorn;ou were wood</L>
<L>Be maister of my body and my good</L>
<L>That oon &thorn;ou schalt forgo maugre &thorn;in ey&yogh;en</L>
<L N="316">What helpe&thorn; it on me enquere and spyen</L>
<L>I trowe &thorn;ough &thorn;ou woldest loke me in &thorn;i cheste</L>
<L>&thorn;ou scholdest seie wyf go where &thorn;e leste</L>
<L>Take youre disporte I wol not leue no tales</L>
<L N="320">I knowe &yogh;ow for a good wyf dame Alis</L>
<L>We loue no man &thorn;at take&thorn; keepe or charge</L>
<L>Where &thorn;at we go we wole be at oure large</L>
<L>Of alle men blessed mote he be</L>
<L N="324">The wise astrologien dann ptholome</L>
<L>That sei&thorn; &thorn;is prouerbe in his almageste</L>
<L>Of alle men his wisdam is hyeste<MILESTONE N="108b" UNIT="folio"></L>
