<HEAD>[The Wrangle between the Summoner and Friar.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>The frere lowh whan he ha&thorn; herd al &thorn;is</L>
<L>Now dame quod he so haue I ioye or blis</L>
<L>This is a long preamble of a tale</L>
<L N="832">And whan &thorn;is somnour herde &thorn;e freere gale /</L>
<L>Lo quod &thorn;e somnour goddes armes tuo</L>
<L>A freere wille entremette him euermo</L>
<L>lo goode men a flye and eek a freere</L>
<L N="836">Wille falle in euery dissche and eek/ matiere /</L>
<L>What spekest &thorn;ou of preambulacion</L>
<L>What amble or trotte or pees or go sit doun</L>
<L>Thou lettest/ oure disport in &thorn;is manere /</L>
<L N="840">&yogh;e woltow so &thorn;ou sompnour quod &thorn;e ffrere /</L>
<L>Now by my fay I schal er &thorn;at I go</L>
<L>Telle of a Somnour such a tale or tuo</L>
<L>That alle &thorn;e folk schulle laughen in &thorn;is place</L>
<L N="844">Now elles frere I beschrewe &thorn;y face</L>
<L>Quod &thorn;is somnour and I byschrewe me /</L>
<L>But if I telle &thorn;e tales tuo or &thorn;re</L>
<L>Of freres or I come to Sydyngborne</L>
<L N="848">&thorn;at I schal make &thorn;in herte for to morne
<PB REF="00000265.tif" N="237"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="358"></L>
<L>ffor wel I wot &thorn;y pacience is gon</L>
<L>Oure hoste cryde pees and &thorn;at anon</L>
<L>And seyde lat &thorn;e womman telle hir tale /</L>
<L N="852">Ye faren as folk &thorn;at dronken ben of ale</L>
<L>Do dame telle for&thorn; youre tale and &thorn;at is beste</L>
<L>Al redy sire quod sche right as yow leste</L>
<L>[<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS cut away. lf</I> 101b, <I>bk</I></NOTE>If I have licens o]f &thorn;is wor&thorn;i frere</L>
<L N="856">[<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS cut away. lf</I> 101b, <I>bk</I></NOTE>Yis dame telle] for&thorn; &thorn;i tale I wol here
</L>
</LG>

