<L N="2052">&thorn;ey in &thorn;e gardyn parformed han and spedde</L>
<L>And in &thorn;is wise many a mery day</L>
<L>lyuede &thorn;is Ianuare and freissche may</L>
<L>But worldly ioye may nou&yogh;t alwey endure</L>
<L N="2056">To Ianuare ne to no worldly creature<MILESTONE N="155b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>O sodeyn happ O &thorn;ou fortune vnstable /</L>
<L>I-like to &thorn;e scorpion vnstable /</L>
<L>That flaterest wi&thorn; &thorn;in heed whan &thorn;ou wolt stynge</L>
<L N="2060">Thyn tayl is de&thorn; &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;in enuenemynge</L>
<L>O brutel ioye O swete poyson queynte</L>
<L>O mustier &thorn;at sotilly canst peynte</L>
<L>&thorn;ine &yogh;iftes vnder &thorn;e hewe of stedefastnesse</L>
<L N="2064">&thorn;at &thorn;ou disceyuedest bo&thorn;e more and lesse
<PB REF="00000371.tif" N="344"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="466"></L>
<L>Why hast &thorn;ou Ianuare &thorn;us deceyued</L>
<L>And haddist him for &thorn;i fulle frend receyued</L>
<L>And now &thorn;ou hast byraft him bo&thorn;e his eyen</L>
<L N="2068">ffor sorwe of which desire&thorn; he to deyen</L>
<L>Allas &thorn;is noble Ianuare &thorn;at is so fre</L>
<L>Amydde his lust and his prosperite</L>
<L>Is woxen blynde and al sodeynly</L>
<L N="2072">his de&thorn; &thorn;erfore desire&thorn; he outrely</L>
<L>And &thorn;er wi&thorn; al &thorn;e fyr of Ielousye</L>
<L>leste &thorn;at his wijf schulde falle in som folye</L>
<L>So brent his herte &thorn;at he wolde fayn</L>
<L N="2076">That som man bo&thorn;e hire and him hadde slayn</L>
<L>ffor neuer [after] his de&thorn; ne in his lyf</L>
<L>Ne wolde he &thorn;at sche were loue ne wyf</L>
<L>But euer lyue as a wydewe in clo&thorn;es blake</L>
<L N="2080">Soule as &thorn;e turtil do&thorn; &thorn;at ha&thorn; lost hire make /</L>
<L>But at &thorn;e laste after a mon&thorn;e or tweye</L>
<L>his sorwe gan to swage so&thorn; to seye</L>
<L>ffor when he wiste it/ may non o&thorn;er be</L>
<L N="2084">he paciently took his aduersite</L>
<L>Saf out of doute may he nou&yogh;t forgon</L>
<L>&thorn;at he nas Ielous euermore in oon</L>
<L>Which Ielousie it was so outrageous</L>
<L N="2088">&thorn;at nei&thorn;er in halle ne in non o&thorn;er hous</L>
<L>he nolde suffre hire for to ryde ne go</L>
<L>Ne in non o&thorn;er place neuer &thorn;e mo</L>
<L>But if &thorn;at he hadde hond on hire alway</L>
<L N="2092">ffor which ful ofte wepe&thorn; freisshe may<MILESTONE N="156a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>That loue&thorn; Damyan so benignely</L>
<L>&thorn;at sche moot ey&thorn;er deye sodeinly</L>
<L>Or elles sche mote han him at hire leste</L>
<L N="2096">sche wayte&thorn; whan hir herte wolde toberste</L>
<L>vpon &thorn;at o&thorn;er syde Damyan</L>
<L>Bycomen is &thorn;e sorwfulleste man</L>
<L>&thorn;at euere was for nei&thorn;er night nor day</L>
<L N="2100">Ne might he speke a word to freisshe may
<PB REF="00000372.tif" N="345"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="467"></L>
<L>As to his purpos of no such matiere /</L>
<L>But if &thorn;at Ianuarie most it here /</L>
<L>&thorn;at hadde oon hond on hir euer mo</L>
<L N="2104">And na&thorn;eles by wrytyng to and fro</L>
<L>And pryue signes wist he what sche ment/</L>
<L>And sche knew of &thorn;e signe of his entent</L>
<L>O Ianuarie what mighte &thorn;e affayle /</L>
<L N="2108">&thorn;ou mightest see as fer as schippes sayle</L>
<L>ffor a[s] good is a blynd disceyued be</L>
<L>As to be deceyued whan a man may se</L>
<L>Lo argus which &thorn;at hadde an C. eyen</L>
<L N="2112">ffor al &thorn;at euer he cou&thorn;e poure or prien</L>
<L>&yogh;it was he blent and god wot so ben mo</L>
<L>&thorn;at wenyn wisly &thorn;at it nys nat so</L>
<L>Passe ouer is an ese and say nomore</L>
<L N="2116">This freissche may of which I spak of yore</L>
<L>In warm wax ha&thorn; emprynted &thorn;is cliket</L>
<L>&thorn;at Ianuarye bar of &thorn;is smale wyket</L>
<L>By which vnto his gardyn ofte he wente</L>
<L N="2120">And Damyan &thorn;at knew hire entente</L>
<L>&thorn;e clyket countrefeted priuily</L>
<L>Ther nys no more to say but hastyly</L>
<L>Som wonder by his cliket schal betyde /</L>
<L N="2124">Which &yogh;e schullen heere if &yogh;e woln abyde</L>
<L>O noble Ovyde so&thorn; saist &thorn;ou god wot</L>
<L>What sleight is it &thorn;ough it be long and hoot</L>
<L>That he nyl fynde it out in som manere</L>
<L>By Pyramus and Thysbe may men leere<MILESTONE N="156b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;ough &thorn;ey were kepte ful longe strei&yogh;t ouer al</L>
<L>&thorn;ey ben acorded rownynge &thorn;urgh a wal</L>
<L>&thorn;er is no wight cou&thorn;e han founde out such a slei&yogh;te</L>
<L N="2132">But now to purpos er &thorn;at dayes ey&yogh;te</L>
<L>Were passed or &thorn;e mon&thorn;e of Iuyl byfille</L>
<L>&thorn;at Ianuarye ha&thorn; caught so gret a wille</L>
<L>&thorn;urgh eggyng of his wijf him for to pleye</L>
<L N="2136">In his gardyn and no wight but &thorn;ey tweye
<PB REF="00000373.tif" N="346"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="468"></L>
<L>That in a morwe vnto his may sayde he</L>
<L>Rise vp my wijf/ my loue my lady fre</L>
<L>&thorn;e turtlis voys is herd my doufe sweete</L>
<L N="2140">The wynter is gon with alle his reynes weete</L>
<L>Com for&thorn; now wi&thorn; &thorn;in eyen columbyne</L>
<L>how fairer ben &thorn;y brestes &thorn;an is wyne</L>
<L>&thorn;e gardyn is enclosed al aboute</L>
<L N="2144">Come for&thorn; my white spouse out of doute</L>
<L>&thorn;ou hast me wounded in myn herte O wyf</L>
<L>No spotte in &thorn;e nas in al &thorn;y lyf</L>
<L>Com for&thorn; and let vs taken oure disport</L>
<L N="2148">I chees &thorn;e for my wyff and my confort</L>
<L>Suche olde lowde wordes vsed he</L>
<L>On damyan a signe made sche</L>
<L>That he schulde go biforn wi&thorn; his clyket</L>
<L N="2152">&thorn;is damyan ha&thorn; opened &thorn;e wyket</L>
<L>And in he sterte and &thorn;at in such manere</L>
<L>&thorn;at no wight might it se ne heere</L>
<L>And stille he sitt vnder a bussch anon</L>
<L N="2156">This Ianuare so blynd as is a stoon</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; mayus in his hond and no wight mo</L>
<L>In to his freisshe gardyn is he go</L>
<L>And clapte to &thorn;e wyket sodeynly</L>
<L N="2160">Now wiff quod he her nys but &thorn;ou and I</L>
<L>&thorn;at art &thorn;e creature &thorn;at I best loue</L>
<L>ffor by &thorn;at lord &thorn;at sitt vs alle aboue</L>
<L>I hadde leuer deyen on a knyf</L>
<L N="2164">Then &thorn;e offenden deere trewe wyf<MILESTONE N="157a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>ffor goddes sake &thorn;enk how I &thorn;e chees</L>
<L>Nou&yogh;t for no coueytise dowteles /</L>
<L>But oonly for &thorn;e loue I hadde to &thorn;e</L>
<L N="2168">And &thorn;ough &thorn;at I be olde and may nou&yogh;t se</L>
<L>Be to me trewe and I wol telle &yogh;ou why</L>
<L>Certes &thorn;re &thorn;inges scholden &yogh;e wynne &thorn;erby</L>
<L>ffirst loue of crist and to &yogh;our self honour</L>
<L N="2172">And al myn heritage toun and tour
<PB REF="00000374.tif" N="347"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="469"></L>
<L>I &yogh;iue it &yogh;ow make&thorn; Chartres as &yogh;ou leste</L>
<L>This schal be do to morwe er sonnes reste</L>
<L>So wisly god my soule bringe in blisse</L>
<L N="2176">And preye &yogh;ou on couenaunt &thorn;at &yogh;e me kisse</L>
<L>And &thorn;ough &thorn;at I be Ielous wyte me nou&yogh;t</L>
<L>&yogh;e ben so deepe enprynted in my &thorn;ou&yogh;t</L>
<L>&thorn;at whan &thorn;at I considere &yogh;our beaute</L>
<L N="2180">And &thorn;er wi&thorn; al &thorn;e vnlikly elde of me</L>
<L>I may nou&yogh;t certes &thorn;ough I schulde deye</L>
<L>ffor-bere to ben out of &yogh;our companye</L>
<L>ffor verray loue &thorn;is is wi&thorn;outen doute</L>
<L N="2184">Now kisse me wijf and let vs rome aboute</L>
<L>&para; This freissche may whan sche &thorn;is wordes herde/</L>
<L>Benignely to Ianuarye answerde</L>
<L>But first and forward sche bygan to weepe</L>
<L N="2188">I haue quod sche a soule for to keepe</L>
<L>As wel as &yogh;e and also myn honour</L>
<L>And of my wifhede &thorn;ilke tendre flour</L>
<L>Which &thorn;at I haue asseured in &yogh;our hand</L>
<L N="2192">Whan &thorn;at &thorn;e prest to yow my body band</L>
<L>Wher-fore I wol answere in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; &thorn;e leue of &yogh;ou my lord so deere</L>
<L>I pray god &thorn;at neuer dawe &thorn;at day</L>
<L N="2196">&thorn;at I ne sterue as foule as womman may</L>
<L>If euer I do vnto my kynne &thorn;at schame /</L>
<L>O&thorn;er elles I empeyre so my name /</L>
<L>&thorn;at y be fals and if I do &thorn;at lak</L>
<L N="2200">To strype me and putte me in a sakk<MILESTONE N="157b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And in &thorn;e nexte ryuer do me drenche</L>
<L>I am a gentil womman and no wenche</L>
<L>Why speke &yogh;e &thorn;us but men ben euer vntrewe</L>
<L N="2204">And wommen han reproef of &yogh;ou ay newe</L>
<L>&yogh;e can non o&thorn;er contynaunce I leeue</L>
<L>But speke to vs as vntriste and in repreue</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word sche saugh wher damyan</L>
<L N="2208">Sat in &thorn;e bussh and knelen he bigan
<PB REF="00000375.tif" N="348"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="470"></L>
<L>And wi&thorn; hire fynger signes made sche</L>
<L>&thorn;at Damyan schulde clymbe vpon a tree</L>
<L>&thorn;at charged was wi&thorn; fruyt and vp he wente</L>
<L N="2212">ffor verrayly he knew al hire entente</L>
<L>And euery signe &thorn;at sche cou&thorn;e make</L>
<L>Wel bet &thorn;an Ianuarye hir owne make</L>
<L>ffor in a lettre sche hadde told him al</L>
<L N="2216">Of &thorn;is matiere how he worche schal</L>
<L>And &thorn;us I lete him sitte in &thorn;e Pyry</L>
<L>And Ianuarye and mayus rownynge myry</L>
<L>&para; Bright was &thorn;e day and blew &thorn;e firmament</L>
<L N="2220">Phebus of gold doun ha&thorn; his stremes sent</L>
<L>To gladen euery flour wi&thorn; his warmnesse</L>
<L>he was &thorn;at tyme in Gemynys as I gesse</L>
<L>But litel fro his declynacion</L>
<L N="2224">Of Cancer Iouys exaltacion</L>
<L>And so bifelle &thorn;at in a bright morwetyde</L>
<L>&thorn;at in &thorn;e gardyn on &thorn;at fer&thorn;er syde /</L>
<L>Pluto &thorn;at is &thorn;e king of fayerye</L>
<L N="2228">And many a lady in his companye</L>
<L>ffolwyng his wyf &thorn;e queene proserpyna</L>
<L>Which &thorn;at he rauyssched out of Proserpyna</L>
<L>Whiles &thorn;at sche gaderede floures in a mede</L>
<L N="2232">In Claudian &yogh;e may &thorn;e storyes rede</L>
<L>how in his grysly carte he hire fette</L>
<L>This kyng of fayerie a doun him sette</L>
<L>vpon a benche of/ toruys freissch and grene</L>
<L N="2236">And right anon seyde he &thorn;us to his queene<MILESTONE N="158a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>My wijf quod he &thorn;at may no wight seye nay</L>
<L>&thorn;e experiens proue&thorn; it euery day</L>
<L>&thorn;e tresoun which &thorn;at womman do&thorn; to man</L>
<L N="2240">Ten hundred &thorn;ousand tellen I can /</L>
<L>Notable of &yogh;our vntrou&thorn;e and brytilnes</L>
<L>O Salamon richest of alle richesse</L>
<L>ffulfild of sapience and of worldly glorie</L>
<L N="2244">fful wor&thorn;y ben &thorn;yne wordes to memorie
<PB REF="00000376.tif" N="349"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="471"></L>
<L>To euery wight &thorn;at witt and reson can</L>
<L>&thorn;us preise&thorn; he &yogh;it &thorn;e bounte of man</L>
<L>Among a &thorn;ousand men &yogh;it fond I on</L>
<L N="2248">But of alle wommen fond he neuer noon</L>
<L>&thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e king &thorn;at knowe&thorn; &yogh;oure wickednes /</L>
<L>And Ihesus filius Cyrak as I ges /</L>
<L>Ne speke&thorn; of &yogh;ou but seeldyn reuerens</L>
<L N="2252">A wilde fuyre a corumpte pestilens</L>
<L>So falle vpon &yogh;our bodyes &yogh;it to nyght</L>
<L>Ne se &yogh;e nought &thorn;is honurable knight</L>
<L>By cause allas &thorn;at he is blynd and old</L>
<L N="2256">his owne man schal make him kokewold</L>
<L>Lo wher he sitte &thorn;e lecchour in &thorn;e tree</L>
<L>Now wol I graunte of myn mageste</L>
<L>vnto &thorn;is olde blynde wor&thorn;y knight</L>
<L N="2260">&thorn;at he schal han a&yogh;ein his ey&yogh;en sight</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at his wijf wolde don him vylenye</L>
<L>&thorn;an schal he knowe al hire harlottrie</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e in repreef of hire and o&thorn;er mo</L>
<L N="2264">&yogh;e schal quod Proserpyn and wol &yogh;e so</L>
<L>Now by mo moodres syres soule I swere</L>
<L>&thorn;at I schal &yogh;euyn hire suffisaunt answere</L>
<L>And alle wommen after for &yogh;our sake /</L>
<L N="2268">&thorn;at &thorn;ough &thorn;ey ben in eny gilt y-take</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; face bold &thorn;ei scholden hemself excuse</L>
<L>And bere hem doun &thorn;at wolden hem accuse /</L>
<L>ffor lakke of answere non of hem scholde deyen</L>
<L>Al hadde &yogh;e seye a &thorn;ing wi&thorn; bo&thorn;e &yogh;our ey&yogh;en<MILESTONE N="158b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&yogh;it schullen we so visagen it hardyly</L>
<L>And weepe and swere and chide subtyly</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e schuln ben as lewed as here gees</L>
<L N="2276">What rekke&thorn; me of &yogh;our auctoritees</L>
<L>I wot wel &thorn;is Iewe &thorn;is Salamon</L>
<L>ffand of vs wommen fooles many oon</L>
<L>But &thorn;ough &thorn;at he ne fond no good womman</L>
<L N="2280">&thorn;er ha&thorn; I-founde many ano&thorn;er man
<PB REF="00000377.tif" N="350"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="472"></L>
<L>Wommen ful trewe ful good ful vertuous</L>
<L>Witnesse on hem &thorn;at dwellen in cristes hous</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; martirdom &thorn;ey prouyd hir<NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS h]</NOTE> constance</L>
<L N="2284">&thorn;e Romayne Iestes maken remembrance</L>
<L>Of many a verray trewe wijf also</L>
<L>but sire ne be&thorn; nou&yogh;t wro&thorn; as be it so</L>
<L>&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at he seyde he fond no good womman</L>
<L N="2288">I pray &yogh;ou take &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e man</L>
<L>he mente &thorn;us &thorn;at in souerayne bounte</L>
<L>Nis non but god but ney&thorn;er he ne sche</L>
<L>Ey for verray god &thorn;at nys but oon</L>
<L N="2292">What make &yogh;e so moche of Salamon</L>
<L>What &thorn;ough he made a temple goddes hous</L>
<L>What &thorn;ough he were riche and glorious</L>
<L>So made he a temple of false godis</L>
<L N="2296">Who mighte do a &thorn;ing &thorn;at more forbode is</L>
<L>Parde as fayr as he his name in-plastre</L>
<L>he was a lecchour and an ydolastre</L>
<L>And in his eelde he verry god forsook</L>
<L N="2300">And if &thorn;at god ne hadde as sei&thorn; &thorn;e book</L>
<L>y-spared him for his fadres sake he scholde</L>
<L>haue lost his regne sonner &thorn;an he wolde</L>
<L>I sette nou&yogh;t of alle &thorn;e vylenye</L>
<L N="2304">&thorn;at &yogh;e of wommen wite a bottirflye</L>
<L>I am a womman needes moot I speke</L>
<L>O&thorn;er elles swelle til myn herte breke</L>
<L>ffor si&thorn;enes he seyde &thorn;at we ben Iangeleresses</L>
<L N="2308">As euer mote I brouke bo&thorn;e my tresses<MILESTONE N="159a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>I schal not spare for no curtesye</L>
<L>To speke him harm &thorn;at wolde vs vilanye</L>
<L>Dame quod &thorn;is pluto be no lengere wro&thorn;</L>
<L N="2312">I &yogh;iue it vp but se&thorn;ens I swor myn o&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at I wolde graunten him his sight a&yogh;ein</L>
<L>My word schal stonde &thorn;at warne I &thorn;e certayn</L>
<L>I am a king it sitt me nou&yogh;t to lye</L>
<L N="2316">And I quod sche a queen of fayerye
<PB REF="00000378.tif" N="350*"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="473"></L>
<L>hire answere sche schal haue I vndertake</L>
<L N="2318">let vs no more wordes make<NOTE PLACE="end">[<I>For the rest of the Tale (from MS Arch. Seld. B.</I> 14) <I>see the Appendix.</I>]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
