<DIV2 TYPE="tale"><PB REF="00000379.tif" N="351">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="500">
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[THE PROEM.]</HEAD>
<HEAD>&para; The p[ro]loge of &thorn;e ffrankeleyn</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Thise olde gentile britouns in here dayes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 159</NOTE></L>
<L>Of diuerse auentures maden layes</L>
<L>Rymeden in here firste britoun tonge</L>
<L N="712">Whiche layes with here instrumentz &thorn;ey songe</L>
<L>O&thorn;er elles radden hem for here plesaunce</L>
<L>And on of hem haue I in remembraunce</L>
<L>Which I schal seye wi&thorn; as good wille as I can</L>
<L N="716">But sires by cause &thorn;at I am a burel man</L>
<L>At my begynnyng first I &yogh;ou beseche</L>
<L>haue&thorn; me excused of my rude speche</L>
<L>I lerned neuer rethorik certayn</L>
<L N="720">&thorn;ing &thorn;at I speke it mot be bare and playn</L>
<L>I slepte neuer on &thorn;e mount of pernaso</L>
<L>Ne neuer lered Marcus Thullius ne Cithero</L>
<L>Colours of Rethorik ne knowe I non wi&thorn;outen drede</L>
<L N="724">But suche coloures as growen in &thorn;e mede</L>
<L>O&thorn;ir elles suche as men dye or peynte</L>
<L>Colours of Rethorik ben me to queynte</L>
<L>Myn spyrit fele&thorn; nought of such matere</L>
<L N="728">But if &yogh;e luste my tale schul &yogh;e not here</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[THE TALE.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="730">Ther was a knight &thorn;at loued and did his peyne</L>
<L N="729">In amoryke &thorn;at cleped is Briteyne</L>
<L>To seruen a lady in his beste wise</L>
<L N="732">And many a labour and many a gret emprise
