<DIV2 TYPE="tale"><PB REF="00000514.tif" N="486"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="199">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>NO more of &thorn;is for goddes dignite<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 210, <I>back</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Quo&thorn; oure hoste for &thorn;ou makest me</L>
<L>So wery of &thorn;y lewednes</L>
<L N="2112">That also wisly god me bles</L>
<L>Myn eres ake of &thorn;in darsty speche<NOTE PLACE="marg">go on to</NOTE><MILESTONE N="217a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Now such a rymere &thorn;e deuel y beteche</L>
<L>This may be wel rym dogerell quod he</L>
<L N="2116">Why so quod I why wilt &thorn;ou lette me</L>
<L>More of my tale &thorn;an ano&thorn;er man</L>
<L>Se&thorn;ens it is &thorn;e beste Rym I can</L>
<L>By god quod he pleynly I &thorn;e say</L>
<L N="2120">&thorn;ou schalt no lenger rymen heere to day</L>
<L>Thow dost nought elles but dispendest tyme</L>
<L>Sire at O word &thorn;ou schalt no lengere ryme</L>
<L>Let se whe&thorn;er &thorn;ou canst telle ought in geste</L>
<L N="2124">Or telle in prose somwhat at &thorn;e leste</L>
<L>In which &thorn;er be som mer&thorn;e and som doctrine</L>
<L>Gladly quod I by goddes swete pyne</L>
<L>I wol &yogh;ou telle a litel &thorn;ing in prose</L>
<L N="2128">&thorn;at oughte like &yogh;ou as I suppose /</L>
<L>Or elles certeyn &yogh;e ben to daungerous</L>
<L>It is a moral tale vertuous</L>
<L>Al be it tolde somtyme in sondry wyse</L>
<L N="2132">Of sondry folk as I schal &yogh;ou deuyse</L>
<L>As &thorn;us &yogh;e wote euery euaungeliste</L>
<L>That telle&thorn; vs of ihesu criste</L>
<L>Ne sai&thorn; nou&yogh;t al &thorn;ing as his felawe do&thorn;</L>
<L N="2136">But natheles here sentence is al so&thorn;</L>
<L>And all acorden as in here sentence</L>
<L>Al be &thorn;er in here tellyng difference
<PB REF="00000515.tif" N="487"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="200"></L>
<L>ffor some of hem seyn more and some lesse</L>
<L N="2140">Whan &thorn;ey his pytous passioun expresse</L>
<L>I mene of mark matheu luke and Iohn</L>
<L>But douteles here sentence is al on</L>
<L>Therfore lordinges all I &yogh;ou beseche</L>
<L N="2144">If &thorn;at &yogh;e &thorn;inke I varie in my speche</L>
<L>As &thorn;us if &thorn;at I telle somwhat more</L>
<L>Of prouerbis &thorn;en &yogh;e haue herd byfore</L>
<L>Comprehendit in &thorn;is litel tretis heere</L>
<L N="2148">To enforce with &thorn;effecte of my matiere</L>
<L>And &thorn;ough I nadde<NOTE PLACE="marg">[nat <I>in a later hand</I>]</NOTE> &thorn;e same wordes saye<MILESTONE N="217b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As &yogh;e han herd &yogh;it to alle &yogh;ou I praye</L>
<L>Blame&thorn; me nought for as in my sentence</L>
<L N="2152">&YOGH;e schal nought fynde mochil difference /</L>
<L>ffro &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e tretys lyyte<NOTE PLACE="marg">[lite <I>in a later hand</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L>After &thorn;e which &thorn;is mery tale I wryte</L>
<L>And<NOTE PLACE="marg">[&thorn;erfore <I>added on margin of MS in another hand</I>]</NOTE> herkene what I schal seye</L>
<L N="2156">And let me telle my tale I &yogh;ou preye /
</L>
</LG>

