] &para; As wel schulde &yogh;e gouerne &yogh;ou and kepe &yogh;ou in such a wyse &thorn;at men clepe &yogh;ou nou&yogh;t to large [2811] &para; &thorn;erfore Tullius <MILESTONE N="230b" UNIT="folio">sai&thorn; &para; The goodes he sai&thorn; of &thorn;in hous schulde not ben hydde ne kepte in cloos but &thorn;at &thorn;ay mighte ben opened wi&thorn; pitee and with debonairtee [2812] &thorn;at is to say to &yogh;euen hem part &thorn;at han gret neede [2813] 
<PB REF="00000555.tif" N="527"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="240"> &para; Ne &thorn;ine goodes schullen not ben so opene to ben euery mannes goodes [2814] &para; afterward in getynge of &yogh;our richesses &para; And in vsynge hem &yogh;e schuln alway haue &thorn;re &thorn;inges in &yogh;oure herte [2815] [<I>c'est assavoir, Dieu, conscience, et bonne fame, et renomm&eacute;e</I>. [2816] <I>Tu dois doncques avoir Dieu en ton cuer</I> (Le M&eacute;nagier, i. 224)] [2817] &para; And for no richesse &yogh;e schuln doon no &thorn;ing &thorn;at may be displesaunce to god &thorn;at is &yogh;oure creatour and &yogh;oure maker [2818] &para; ffor after &thorn;e word of Salamon &para; hit is bettre to haue a luytel good wi&thorn; &thorn;e loue of god. [2819] &thorn;an to haue mochil good and tresour and lese &thorn;e loue of his lord god [2820] &para; And &thorn;e prophete sai&thorn;. &thorn;at better it is to ben a good man and haue lytel good and tresour. [2821] &thorn;an to be halden a schrewe and to haue gret richesse [2822] &para; &yogh;et say I for&thorn;ermore &thorn;at &yogh;e schuln don &yogh;oure busynesse to geten &yogh;ou richesse [2823] So &thorn;at &yogh;e geten hem wi&thorn; good conscience [2824] &para; And &thorn;e appostel sai&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;er is no &thorn;ing in &thorn;is world of which we schulden haue so gret ioye; as when oure conscience bere&thorn; vs good witnesse [2825] &para; And &thorn;e wise man sai&thorn; &para; The substaunce of a man is ful good when synne is nought in mannes conscience [2826] &para; Aftirward in getyng of &yogh;oure Richesses and in vsynge of hem; [2827] &yogh;e moste haue gret busynesse and gret diligence that &yogh;oure goode name be alwey kepte and conserued [2828] &para; ffor Sala|mon sai&thorn; &para; &thorn;at better it is and more auayle&thorn; a man to haue good name &thorn;en to haue grete richesses [2829] &para; And &thorn;erfore he sai&thorn; in ano&thorn;er place &para; Do gret diligence sai&thorn; Salamon