<PB REF="00000556.tif" N="528"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="241"> [2833] &para; And &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; seint austyn &thorn;at &thorn;er ben tuo &thorn;inges &thorn;at ben necessary and needfulle [2834] &para; And &thorn;at is good consciens [2835] to &thorn;in owne persone inward and good loos ffor &thorn;in neyhebour outward [2836] &para; And he &thorn;at truste&thorn; him so mechel in his goode conscience [2837] &thorn;at he displese&thorn; and sette&thorn; it at nou&yogh;t his good name or loos and rekke&thorn; nou&yogh;t &thorn;at he kepe&thorn; nou&yogh;t his good name nys but a cruel cherle</P>
<P>[2838] &para; Sire now haue I schewed &yogh;ow how &yogh;e schuln doon in getynge of richesse and how &yogh;e schuln vsen hem [2839] &para; And I se wel &thorn;at for &thorn;e truste &thorn;at &yogh;e han in richesse &yogh;e wollen moeue bataile <MILESTONE N="231a" UNIT="folio">and werre [2840] &para; I counsele &yogh;ou &thorn;at &yogh;e begynne no werre in truste of &yogh;oure richesses &para; ffor &thorn;ey sufficen nou&yogh;t werres to meyn|tene [2841] &para; And &thorn;erfore sai&thorn; a Philosophre &para; That a man desire&thorn; and wol algates han werre schal neuer haue sufficaunce [2842] &para; ffor &thorn;e richere &thorn;at he is &thorn;e gretter despenses moot he make if he wole haue wor|schipe and victory [2843] &para; And Salamon saith &thorn;at &thorn;e grettere richesse &thorn;at a man ha&thorn; &thorn;e more dispendoures he ha&thorn; [2844] &para; And deere sir al be it so &thorn;at for &yogh;oure richesses &yogh;e may han moche folk [2845] &para; &yogh;et byhoue&thorn; it nought ne it is nou&yogh;t good to begynne werre wher as &yogh;e may in o&thorn;er manere haue pees vnto &yogh;oure worschipe and profyt [2846] &para; ffor &thorn;e victories of Batailles &thorn;at ben in &thorn;is world li&thorn; nou&yogh;t in gret nombre of multitude of poeple ne in &thorn;e vertu of man; [2847] but it lith in &thorn;e wille and in &thorn;e hande of our lord ihesu crist // [2848] And &thorn;erfore Iudas Makabeus which was goddes knight [2849] when he schulde fighten a&yogh;eins his aduersaries &thorn;at hadde a gretter nombre &amp; a gretter mul|titude of folk and strenger &thorn;en was &thorn;e poeple of Macha|bee [2850] &para; &yogh;et he recomforted his litel companye and sayde right in &thorn;is wise [2851] &para; As lightly quod he may our lord god almighty &yogh;eue victory to fewe folk 
<PB REF="00000557.tif" N="529"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="242"> as to many folk [2852] &para; ffor &thorn;e victory of bataile come&thorn; nou&yogh;t by gret nombre of poeple; [2853] but it come&thorn; fro oure lord of heuene // [2854] &para; And deere sire for as mochil as &thorn;er is no man certein if it be wor&thorn;y &thorn;at god &yogh;eue him victory . . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> or nou&yogh;t. after &thorn;at Salomon sei&thorn; [2855] &para; &thorn;erfore euery man schulde gretly drede werres to begynne [2856] &para; And by cause &thorn;at in batailles schuln fallen many periles [2857] &para; And happe&thorn; o&thorn;erwhile &thorn;at as sone is &thorn;e grete man slayn as &thorn;e litel man [2858] &para; And as it is writen in &thorn;e seconde book of kynges &para; The deedes of batailles ben aduenturous and vncertein [2859] ffor as lightly as is oon y-hurt wi&thorn; a spere as ano&thorn;er. [2860] and &thorn;erfore is gret perile in werre &para; Therfore schulden men flee and eschewe werre in as mechel as a man may goodly [2861] &para; ffor Salamon sai&thorn; &para; he &thorn;at loue&thorn; perill; schal falle in perille</P>
