<DIV1 N="I" TYPE="group"><PB REF="00000628.tif" N="600"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="589">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>I.</B> FRAGMENT X.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. THE BLANK-PARSON LINK. CORPUS MS. Here bygynne&thorn; &thorn;e prologe of &thorn;e parson</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>[This is really a link between some unwritten Tale and the Parson's. It has been made into the Manciple-Parson Link (or Yeoman-Parson by the Christ-Church MS) by Chaucer's copiers, though not meant for it.]</P><P><I>on leaf</I> 261</P></HEADNOTE>

<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>By &thorn;at &thorn;e maunciple hadde his tale ended<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ca<SUP>m</SUP> xxiiij<SUP>m</SUP></NOTE></L>
<L>The sonne fro &thorn;e sou&thorn; syde is descended</L>
<L>So lowe &thorn;at he was nought to my sight</L>
<L N="4">Degrees xxix as of highte /</L>
<L>Ten of &thorn;e clokke it was so as I gesse /</L>
<L>ffor xj foote a lytel more or lesse</L>
<L>My schadwe was at &thorn;ilke tyme as &thorn;ere /</L>
<L N="8">Of suche feet as my leng&thorn;e parted were /</L>
<L>In six foote equal of proporcion</L>
<L>Ther-wi&thorn; &thorn;e mones exaltacion</L>
<L>I mene libra alwey gan ascende</L>
<L N="12">As we were entryng at a thropes ende</L>
<L>ffor wi&thorn; oure Oste as he was wont to gye</L>
<L>As in &thorn;is caas oure ioly companye /</L>
<L>Sayde in &thorn;is wise lordynges euerychon</L>
<L N="16">Now lakke&thorn; vs no tale more &thorn;an oon</L>
<L>ffulfild is my sentence and my degre</L>
<L>Who wile now telle a tale let se</L>
<L>Almost fulfilled is myn ordynaunce</L>
<L N="20">I pray to god so &yogh;iue him right good chance</L>
<L>&thorn;at telle&thorn; &thorn;is tale to vs lustely</L>
<L>Sire prest quod he art &thorn;ou a vicary</L>
<L>Or art &thorn;ou a person say so&thorn; by &thorn;y fey</L>
<L N="24">Be what &thorn;ou be ne breke nought oure pley
<PB REF="00000629.tif" N="601"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="590"></L>
<L N="25">ffor euery man saue &thorn;ou ha&thorn; told his tale</L>
<L>vnbokele and schewe vs what is in &thorn;y male<MILESTONE N="261b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>ffor trewely me &thorn;enke&thorn; by &thorn;y cheere</L>
<L N="28">Thou scholdest knette vp wel a gret matiere</L>
<L>Telle vs a fable anon for cokkes bones</L>
<L>This person answered al at oones</L>
<L>Thou getest fable non y-tolde for me</L>
<L N="32">ffor Poule &thorn;at write&thorn; vnto Thimothe</L>
<L>Repreue&thorn; hem &thorn;at wayuen so&thorn;fastnesse</L>
<L>And tellen fables and such wrecchednesse</L>
<L>Whi schulde I schewen draff out of my feste /</L>
<L N="36">Whan I may schewen whete if &thorn;at me leste</L>
<L>ffor which I saye if &thorn;at &thorn;ou luste to heere</L>
<L>Moralite and vertuous matiere</L>
<L>And &thorn;enne &thorn;at &yogh;e woln &yogh;iue me audience</L>
<L N="40">I wol ful fayn at cristes reuerence /</L>
<L>Don &yogh;ou plesaunce lefful as I can</L>
<L>But truste&thorn; wel I am a sothryn man</L>
<L>I can nought geste rom ram ruf by lettre</L>
<L N="44">Ne god wot rym holde I but lytel bettre</L>
<L>And &thorn;erfore if &yogh;ou luste I wol nought glose</L>
<L>I wol &yogh;ou telle a mery tale in prose</L>
<L>To knitte vp al &thorn;is feste an ende</L>
<L N="48">And ihesu for his grace witte me sende</L>
<L>To schewe &yogh;ou &thorn;e wey in &thorn;is visage</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ilke parfyt glorious pilgrimage</L>
<L>That highte Ierusalem Celestial</L>
<L N="52">And if &yogh;e vouche sauf anon &yogh;e schal</L>
<L>Bygynne vpon my tale for which I preye</L>
<L>Telle &yogh;oure avis I can no bettre seye</L>
<L>But na&thorn;eles &thorn;is meditacion</L>
<L N="56">I putte it ay vnder correction</L>
<L>Of clerkes for I am nought text wel</L>
<L>I take but &thorn;e sentence trustel wel</L>
<L>&thorn;erfore I make protestacion</L>
<L N="60">That I wol stonde to correction
<PB REF="00000630.tif" N="602"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="591"></L>
<L>Vppon &thorn;is word we han assented sone<NOTE PLACE="marg">[a leaf cut out of the Corpus MS]</NOTE></L>
<L>[for as hit semed / hit was for to doone<MILESTONE UNIT="MS Arch. Seld. B. 14 folio" N="268a"></L>
<L>to enden / in som vertuous sentence</L>
<L N="64">and for to yeve him space / and audience</L>
<L>and bad oure Oste / he shulde to him say</L>
<L>that alle we / to telle his tale him pray</L>
<L>oure Oste had the wordes / for vs alle</L>
<L N="68">sir prest quod he / now faire yow befalle</L>
<L>sey what yow luste / and we wol gladly here</L>
<L>and with that worde / he seide in this manere</L>
<L>telleth quod he / youre meditacioun</L>
<L N="72">but hasteth yow / the sonne wol a-doun</L>
<L>beth fructuous / and that in litel space</L>
<L>and to do wel / god sende yow his grace.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Here endith the parson his prolog]<NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS Arch. Seld. B. 14 <I>extract stops</I>]</NOTE></TRAILER>
</DIV2>
